         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1//5/86. ¶  ¶ Am very glad, dear Mr Barbey, that you are supplementing the great work of the never to be forgotten M. Boissier. ¶  Had he lived I would have sent him my only specimen of the Euphorbia ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.05.01a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Barbey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Conservatoire et Jardin botanique, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1//5/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Am very glad, dear Mr Barbey, that you are supplementing the great work of the never to be forgotten M. Boissier.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Boissier (1862).</p>
               </note> Had he lived I would have sent him my only specimen of the <name key="Euphorbia%20corynoclada">Euphorbia corynoclada</name>, as it would have highly interested him, that being the only large carnulent<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>fleshy?</p>
               </note> species (of the section Euphorbium) indigenous to Australia. Do you care to interchange occasionally a few hundred dried plant with me, Mr Tate's parcel-office affords for this here now cheap facilities.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be worthy of your consideration, to elaborate a statistic of the Flora Orientalis for easy glance over the distribution as I have done in my Census of Australian plants? I am endeavouring, to get Regel or Maximowicz to do something similar for the Russian Flora, — and Hance for the Chinese Flora. Such tabulated indices would facilitate phytogeographic studies very much, not only at home, but also abroad, not only locally but also universally!</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Euphorbia%20corynoclada">Euphorbia corynoclada</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
